# 🎮 Catch Me If You Can – Mini Game

A fun, beginner-friendly browser game inspired by MIT’s game-building concepts. The goal? Try to catch the red square as it jumps around the screen!

---

## 🕹️ Gameplay

- A red square appears at random positions every 2 seconds.
- Click on the red square to "catch" it.
- Every successful click shows an alert and repositions the square.
- Simple yet addictive reflex training!

---

## 🧠 Inspiration

This game is influenced by the logic and creativity of [MIT Scratch](https://scratch.mit.edu) and beginner-friendly programming from MIT’s [Open Learning](https://openlearning.mit.edu/) resources.

